Governing Law
19.2 . With respect to any suit, action or proceedings relating to the Reinsurance Agreement, each Party irrevocably:
Jurisdiction
(a) submits to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of any federal or New York State court located in the City of New York, Borough of Manhattan;
(b) waives any objection which it may have at any time to the laying of venue of any suit, action or proceedings brought in any such court, waives any claim that such proceedings have been brought in an inconvenient forum and further waives the right to object, with respect to such suit, action or proceedings, that such court does not have any jurisdiction over such Party; and
(c) waives any claim to punitive, exemplary or multiplied damages from the other.
